            "text": "; a metaphor which is also used in Greek.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And a line of thirty cubits . . .—Line, i.e., measuring-line, as in Ezekiel 47:3. The Hebrew is qāw. In Kings we read a rare form, qāwèh. The rest of the clause is the same in both texts.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "And a line of thirty cubits",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
